                    The Secretary of State to the
                            Acting Secretary of State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1945Berlinv02</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d724</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">724</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1945-07-16T00:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1945-07-16T23:59:59-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="724" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d724">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 (Potsdam)/7–1645: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 724<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Babelsberg</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-16">July 16,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Victory1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Victory</hi>
                    </gloss> 35. Top secret to Acting Secretary of State.</p>
                <p>British Delegation informs us Department proposes issuing statement July 17th
                    that United States will support Italy’s admission to international organization
                    and has asked British Government to do likewise. Would prefer that you postpone
                    action on this as I desire to <pb facs="0818" n="624" xml:id="pg_624"/> give
                    consideration to some statement regarding Italy into which would be incorporated
                    if possible reference to this subject and to which I would like to consider
                    inviting Soviet Government to join.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
